## Verification tiers (`scripts/verify_tier.py`)

Canonical local runner — prefer over hand-rolling the chain.

| Tier | Steps |
|------|-------|
| **unit** | `count_tests.py` → `unittest discover` |
| **ux** | `build_help.py` → **unit** → `streamlit_smoke.py` |
| **profile** | **ux** → playbook E2E (+ `health_check` for b/c/d) |
| **release** | Full `RELEASE_STEPS`: count_tests, build_help, ruff, mypy, validation_evidence, samples, unittest, streamlit_smoke, E2E chain, health_check |

```powershell
python scripts\verify_tier.py --tier unit
python scripts\verify_tier.py --tier ux
python scripts\verify_tier.py --tier profile --playbook b
python scripts\verify_tier.py --tier release
```

**Release** ≈ CI **quality** gates minus coverage + ubuntu **test**/E2E. Does **not** run **windows-smoke**.

## CI jobs ([`.github/workflows/ci.yml`](.github/workflows/ci.yml))

| Job | Runs | What |
|-----|------|------|
| **quality** | ubuntu, Python 3.11 | ruff lint/format, mypy (production modules), **`build_help.py`**, coverage (`--fail-under=50`), `validation_evidence.py` |
| **test** | matrix Python **3.11–3.13** | samples + **`build_help.py`** + unittest + streamlit_smoke; **full E2E chain on 3.11 only** |
| **windows-smoke** | windows-latest (PRs / pushes) | `build_windows_deploy.ps1 -SkipExe` → asserts `help/index.html` in package → bundled-venv `health_check.py` + `streamlit_smoke.py` |

